lenges of growing up with a rare disease all too well  The    year old was born with Hunter syndrome  a lysosomal storage disorder that affects his bodily systems and physical growth and devel opment    UIC s Division of Specialized Care for Children was a constant presence throughout his childhood and adolescence  providing much needed reassurance to Zayd and his parents  This support gave him hope and put him on the path to helping others  Thank you  Zayd  for sharing your story and giving great advice for youth with special needs  See More UIC Specialized Care For Children   hr Fourteen programs across the country are receiving grants to teach people with autism to code and learn other digital literacy skills Programs Teaching Those With Autism To Code Get Boost See All See More 